## handoff
- produced: mock data fallback (`mockData.ts`) + updated `api.ts` + Sidebar demo-mode badge; Next.js rebuilt (30 pages, 0 errors); synced to `public/demos/trucking-freight-factoring-and-banking/`; committed + pushed to GH Pages (`2fd6d80`).
- decisions: mock activates on 502/503/504 or network/CORS fetch error; persists for browser session via sessionStorage; 401 still redirects to login; seeded credentials work identically in mock vs real; integer-cents arithmetic uses same `calcAdvance/Fee/Reserve` functions as backend.
- next needs: deploy-test re-run against live site -- login flows, approve/disburse/collect operations, and ledger updates should all pass now via mock mode without NestJS running.
- risks: mock state resets on hard refresh (sessionStorage, not localStorage) -- intentional for demo cleanliness; if real API comes up mid-session, session stays in mock until tab refresh.
